Normally I would give this place 4 stars, but because of the coupon deal monday - wednesdays 50% off it bumped it up to 5. Â First of all, the only thing worth buying are the rolls, they are small, innovative and inexpensive, which allows you to buy 3-4 rolls instead of sticking with 2 and hope they are good. The space is small and it takes a while to get your meal, but if you can get there in off hours it is worth the trip. They love spice, so beware, but it does add a bit of flair since most asian places in the area serve most of their food mild, even when they say it is spicy
